notes: Patient presents with elevated blood pressure 150/95. Prescribed lisinopril 10mg daily. Advised on dietary modifications and regular exercise. Follow-up in 4 weeks.
Type 2 diabetes mellitus follow-up. HbA1c 7.2%. Metformin dose increased to 1000mg twice daily. Patient counseled on carbohydrate counting and blood glucose monitoring.
Asthma exacerbation. Patient reports increased wheezing and shortness of breath. Peak flow 60% of predicted. Prescribed prednisone 40mg daily for 5 days and albuterol inhaler.
Lower back pain for 3 weeks. No radiation to legs. Physical exam shows muscle spasm in lumbar region. Prescribed ibuprofen 600mg TID and physical therapy referral.
GERD symptoms with heartburn and regurgitation. Patient reports symptoms worsen after meals. Prescribed omeprazole 20mg daily and lifestyle modifications discussed.
Major depressive episode, moderate severity. PHQ-9 score 14. Started on sertraline 50mg daily. Referred to counseling services. Follow-up in 2 weeks.
Urinary tract infection. Symptoms include dysuria and frequency. Urine dipstick positive for nitrites and leukocytes. Prescribed ciprofloxacin 250mg BID for 3 days.
Conjunctivitis, bilateral. Eyes red and watery with purulent discharge. Prescribed tobramycin ophthalmic drops QID for 7 days. Advised on hygiene measures.
Fever of unknown origin, 101.5°F for 2 days. No other localizing symptoms. Physical exam unremarkable. CBC and blood cultures ordered. Symptomatic treatment advised.
Annual physical examination. Patient reports feeling well. Vital signs normal. Mammogram and colonoscopy up to date. Recommended annual labs and flu vaccination.
Eczema flare-up on arms and legs. Dry, itchy, erythematous patches. Prescribed triamcinolone 0.1% cream BID and recommended fragrance-free moisturizers.
Migraine headache with nausea and photophobia. Episode lasted 8 hours. Prescribed sumatriptan 50mg for acute episodes and discussed trigger avoidance strategies.
Coronary artery disease follow-up. Patient reports occasional chest tightness with exertion. EKG unchanged. Continued on atorvastatin and metoprolol. Stress test scheduled.
Right shoulder pain for 2 months. Limited range of motion. Likely rotator cuff tendinitis. Prescribed naproxen 500mg BID and physical therapy referral.
Shortness of breath on exertion for 1 week. No chest pain or cough. Chest X-ray normal. Echocardiogram ordered to rule out cardiac cause. Follow-up in 1 week.
Constipation for 10 days. Abdominal discomfort and bloating. Recommended increased fiber intake, adequate hydration, and docusate sodium 100mg BID.
Viral upper respiratory infection. Runny nose, sore throat, and mild cough for 3 days. No fever. Symptomatic treatment with rest, fluids, and throat lozenges advised.
Acute vaginitis with itching and discharge. Wet mount shows yeast. Prescribed fluconazole 150mg single dose and advised on cotton underwear and probiotics.
Right ankle sprain from basketball injury yesterday. Moderate swelling and tenderness. X-ray negative for fracture. RICE protocol and ibuprofen 600mg TID prescribed.
Generalized anxiety disorder. Patient reports persistent worry and restlessness. GAD-7 score 12. Started on escitalopram 10mg daily and referred for cognitive behavioral therapy.
Otitis media, right ear. Ear pain and decreased hearing for 2 days. Tympanic membrane erythematous and bulging. Prescribed amoxicillin 500mg TID for 10 days.
Tension headache, bilateral frontal. Present for 4 hours. No neurological deficits. Likely stress-related. Prescribed acetaminophen 650mg q6h PRN and stress management techniques.
Acute pharyngitis. Sore throat and odynophagia for 2 days. Throat erythematous, no exudate. Rapid strep negative. Symptomatic treatment with salt water gargles and analgesics.
Abdominal pain, diffuse, crampy for 6 hours. No nausea or vomiting. Physical exam benign. Likely gastroenteritis. Clear liquids and gradual diet advancement recommended.
Chemotherapy encounter for colon cancer. Cycle 4 of FOLFOX regimen. Pre-chemo labs acceptable. Patient tolerating treatment well with minimal side effects.
Peripheral vascular disease. Claudication in bilateral calves after walking 2 blocks. Ankle-brachial index 0.7. Started on cilostazol 100mg BID and exercise program.
Rheumatoid arthritis follow-up. Morning stiffness 45 minutes, joint swelling in hands. RF positive, CRP elevated. Methotrexate dose increased to 15mg weekly.
Hyperlipidemia. Total cholesterol 280, LDL 190. No family history of CAD. Started on atorvastatin 20mg daily and counseled on dietary modifications.
Chronic kidney disease stage 3. Creatinine 1.8, eGFR 45. Blood pressure well controlled. ACE inhibitor continued. Nephrology referral scheduled.
Presbyopia. Patient reports difficulty reading small print. Vision exam shows decreased near vision. Prescribed reading glasses +2.00 diopters.
Functional dyspepsia. Epigastric pain and bloating after meals for 2 months. No alarm symptoms. H. pylori test negative. Started on famotidine 20mg BID.
Post-traumatic stress disorder following car accident 3 months ago. Nightmares and flashbacks. PCL-5 score 45. Referred to trauma-focused therapy.
Heart failure with reduced ejection fraction. EF 35%. Patient reports dyspnea on exertion and ankle swelling. Furosemide dose increased to 40mg daily.
Insomnia disorder. Difficulty falling asleep and frequent awakenings for 6 weeks. Sleep hygiene counseling provided. Prescribed trazodone 50mg at bedtime.
Atopic dermatitis flare on face and neck. Dry, scaly, erythematous patches. Prescribed hydrocortisone 1% cream BID and recommended gentle skincare routine.
Low back pain radiating to right leg. Positive straight leg raise test. MRI shows L5-S1 disc herniation. Prescribed gabapentin 300mg TID and physical therapy.
Dizziness and lightheadedness for 3 days. No vertigo or hearing loss. Blood pressure and glucose normal. Likely viral labyrinthitis. Meclizine 25mg TID prescribed.
Gastrointestinal bleeding, lower. Hematochezia for 2 days. Hemoglobin 10.2. Colonoscopy scheduled urgently. NPO after midnight, bowel prep instructions given.
COPD exacerbation. Increased dyspnea and sputum production. SpO2 88% on room air. Started on prednisone 40mg daily and azithromycin 500mg daily.
Iron deficiency anemia. Hemoglobin 8.5, ferritin 8. Heavy menstrual periods reported. Started on ferrous sulfate 325mg TID and gynecology referral made.
Osteoarthritis of knee, bilateral. Joint pain and stiffness worse in mornings. X-rays show joint space narrowing. Prescribed celecoxib 200mg daily and knee exercises.
Prediabetes. Fasting glucose 115 mg/dL, HbA1c 6.2%. Counseled on lifestyle modifications including diet and exercise. Follow-up labs in 3 months.
Cerumen impaction, bilateral ears. Decreased hearing and ear fullness. Cerumen removal performed with irrigation. Hearing improved immediately post-procedure.
Benign prostatic hyperplasia. Urinary frequency and weak stream. PSA 2.1. IPSS score 18. Started on tamsulosin 0.4mg daily and advised on fluid timing.
Alcohol use disorder, moderate. AUDIT score 16. Patient motivated for treatment. Referred to addiction counseling and support groups. Thiamine supplementation started.
Secondary malignant neoplasm of lung. Follow-up for metastatic breast cancer. CT chest shows stable pulmonary nodules. Continue current chemotherapy regimen.
Atrial fibrillation, paroxysmal. Episodes of palpitations and dizziness. EKG shows irregular rhythm. Started on metoprolol 25mg BID and warfarin therapy.
Fibromyalgia. Widespread musculoskeletal pain and fatigue for 8 months. Tender points positive. Started on duloxetine 30mg daily and sleep hygiene counseling.
Chronic cough for 6 weeks. Non-productive, worse at night. Chest X-ray normal. Likely post-infectious cough. Prescribed dextromethorphan and honey for symptom relief.
Menopausal syndrome. Hot flashes and night sweats affecting sleep quality. Last menstrual period 14 months ago. Discussed hormone therapy options and lifestyle modifications.
Fracture of right femoral neck from fall. X-rays confirm displaced fracture. Orthopedic surgery consultation arranged for surgical fixation. Pain management initiated.
Acute pancreatitis. Severe epigastric pain radiating to back. Lipase 850 U/L. CT shows pancreatic inflammation. NPO, IV fluids, and pain management started.
Macular degeneration, dry type. Gradual vision loss in both eyes. Fundoscopy shows drusen and pigment changes. Referred to retinal specialist for evaluation.
Diarrhea for 5 days. Watery stools 6-8 times daily. No blood or mucus. Stool culture pending. Advised on fluid replacement and BRAT diet.
Schizophrenia, stable on current medications. No active psychotic symptoms. Medication compliance good. Continue risperidone 4mg daily and monthly follow-ups.
Varicose veins of lower extremity. Aching and heaviness in legs, worse with standing. Compression stockings recommended and vascular surgery referral made.
Allergic reaction to shellfish. Urticaria and mild wheezing 30 minutes after eating shrimp. Treated with diphenhydramine 50mg and albuterol inhaler. EpiPen prescribed.
Kidney stone, right side. Severe flank pain radiating to groin. CT shows 4mm stone in right ureter. Pain management with ketorolac and increased fluid intake.
Multiple sclerosis relapse. New onset numbness in left arm and leg. MRI shows new T2 lesions. Started on high-dose methylprednisolone for 3 days.
Hypothyroidism. Fatigue and weight gain for 3 months. TSH 12.5, T4 low. Started on levothyroxine 50mcg daily. Recheck thyroid function in 6 weeks.
Systemic lupus erythematosus. Joint pain and fatigue. ANA positive 1:320, anti-dsDNA elevated. Started on hydroxychloroquine 400mg daily and prednisone taper.
Prediabetes with impaired glucose tolerance. 2-hour glucose 165 mg/dL on OGTT. Metformin 500mg BID started and diabetes prevention program referral made.
Sensorineural hearing loss, bilateral. Gradual hearing decline over 2 years. Audiometry shows moderate loss. Hearing aid evaluation scheduled with audiology.
Fatty liver disease. Elevated ALT 85, AST 72. Ultrasound shows hepatic steatosis. Weight loss counseling provided and alcohol cessation advised.
Autism spectrum disorder follow-up. 8-year-old patient doing well in special education program. Social skills improving. Continue behavioral therapy and family support.
Atherosclerosis, generalized. Carotid ultrasound shows 40% stenosis bilaterally. Started on aspirin 81mg daily and atorvastatin 40mg daily for vascular protection.
Nausea and vomiting for 24 hours. No fever or diarrhea. Likely viral gastroenteritis. IV fluids given for dehydration. Ondansetron 4mg prescribed for nausea.
Sacroiliac joint dysfunction. Lower back pain worse with sitting and standing from seated position. Positive FABER test. Physical therapy and SI joint injection recommended.
Edema of lower extremities, bilateral. 2+ pitting edema to mid-calf. Echocardiogram and BNP ordered to evaluate for heart failure. Furosemide 20mg daily started.
Bipolar disorder, currently manic episode. Elevated mood, decreased need for sleep, rapid speech. Lithium level subtherapeutic. Dose increased to 900mg BID.
Breast cancer, right breast. Post-lumpectomy follow-up. Pathology shows invasive ductal carcinoma, ER positive. Oncology referral for adjuvant therapy planning.
Difficulty walking and balance problems. Gait unsteady, wide-based. Neurological exam shows mild ataxia. MRI brain ordered to evaluate for cerebellar pathology.
Diverticulosis of colon. Incidental finding on colonoscopy. No current symptoms. Counseled on high-fiber diet and adequate fluid intake for prevention.
Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo. Episodes of vertigo with head movement. Positive Dix-Hallpike test. Epley maneuver performed with symptom improvement.
Venous insufficiency of lower extremity. Chronic leg swelling and varicose veins. Venous duplex shows reflux in great saphenous vein. Compression therapy initiated.
Hemoptysis, small amount of blood-streaked sputum for 2 days. Chest X-ray shows no acute abnormalities. CT chest ordered to rule out pulmonary pathology.
Anoxic brain injury sequelae. Post-cardiac arrest with mild cognitive impairment. Neuropsychological testing shows memory deficits. Cognitive rehabilitation referral made.
Cutaneous abscess of trunk. 3cm fluctuant mass on back with surrounding erythema. Incision and drainage performed. Culture sent and clindamycin 300mg TID prescribed.
Tremor of hands, bilateral. Fine tremor worse with action, improves with rest. No other neurological symptoms. Likely essential tremor. Propranolol 40mg BID started.
Incomplete uterovaginal prolapse. Pelvic pressure and bulging sensation. Grade 2 cystocele on exam. Pelvic floor exercises taught and pessary fitting scheduled.
Chronic fatigue syndrome. Persistent fatigue for 8 months not improved with rest. Post-exertional malaise present. Sleep study and thyroid function tests ordered.
Systemic lupus erythematosus flare. Joint pain, fatigue, and malar rash. C3, C4 low, anti-dsDNA elevated. Prednisone increased to 20mg daily and rheumatology follow-up.
Urinary retention. Unable to void for 8 hours with bladder distension. Foley catheter placed with 800mL residual. Urology referral for further evaluation.
Epiphora (excessive tearing) bilateral. Chronic tearing and eye irritation. Nasolacrimal duct obstruction suspected. Ophthalmology referral for dacryocystography.
Repeated falls, 3 episodes in past month. Gait assessment shows mild instability. Home safety evaluation recommended and physical therapy referral for fall prevention.
Hemorrhage of anus and rectum. Bright red blood per rectum with bowel movements. External hemorrhoids noted on exam. Sitz baths and topical hydrocortisone prescribed.
Abnormal electrocardiogram. ST depression in leads V4-V6. Patient asymptomatic. Stress test ordered to evaluate for coronary artery disease. Cardiology referral made.
Crepitant synovitis of wrist. Pain and swelling over radial styloid with thumb movement. Positive Finkelstein test. De Quervain tenosynovitis diagnosed. Thumb spica splint applied.
Cardiogenic shock secondary to acute MI. Blood pressure 80/50, poor perfusion. Emergent cardiac catheterization performed with stent placement. ICU admission arranged.
Tinnitus, bilateral. Constant ringing in both ears for 6 months. Audiometry shows mild high-frequency hearing loss. Hearing aid trial and tinnitus masking discussed.
Unspecified coma. Patient found unresponsive. Glasgow Coma Scale 6. CT head negative for acute pathology. Toxicology screen and metabolic panel ordered.
Calcific tendinitis of shoulder. Severe shoulder pain with limited range of motion. X-ray shows calcific deposits in rotator cuff. Steroid injection performed.
Other general symptoms - chronic pain syndrome. Widespread pain affecting daily activities. Pain scale 7/10. Multimodal pain management approach discussed.
Tricuspid valve disorder. Echocardiogram shows moderate tricuspid regurgitation. Patient reports dyspnea on exertion. Cardiology follow-up scheduled for valve assessment.
Localized swelling, mass and lump of trunk. 2cm firm mass in right axilla. Ultrasound shows solid lesion. Surgical consultation for biopsy scheduled.
Tension-type headache, unspecified, not intractable. Daily headaches for 2 months. Stress-related pattern noted. Amitriptyline 25mg at bedtime started for prevention.
Dyspnea, unspecified. Shortness of breath on minimal exertion for 1 week. Chest X-ray shows mild pulmonary edema. Diuretic therapy initiated and cardiology referral made.
Spinal stenosis, lumbar region. Neurogenic claudication with walking. MRI shows moderate central stenosis L3-L4. Physical therapy and epidural injection discussed.
Drug-induced fever. Temperature 101.8°F after starting new antibiotic 3 days ago. Medication discontinued and fever resolved within 24 hours. Alternative antibiotic prescribed.
Encounter for screening for malignant neoplasm of colon. Routine colonoscopy screening at age 50. Procedure completed successfully with no polyps found. Repeat in 10 years.
